  • Constructor Details

    • Vektor

      public Vektor()
      Constructs a new Vektor that WILL NOT carry solutions in the finite field F2. Can be thought of as a subspace of the matrix A, where A is a coefficent matrix of booleans in F2.

    • Vektor

      public Vektor(boolean isSolution)
      Constructs a new Vektor that WILL carry solutions in the finite field F2. Can be thought of as a subspace of the solution set b, where b satifies the equation Ax = b in F2.
      Parameters:
      isSolution - Set to true.

    • areUnique

      public boolean areUnique(Vektor other)
      Examines whether this Vektor and other Vektor are linearly independent. Two vektors are independent if they are not unique.
      Parameters:
      other - Other Vektor Object
      Returns:
      true if independent, false if dependent.

    • setElement

      public void setElement(int index, int missingValue)
      At this index, changes the current value to the element provided. If this index is out of bounds, adds the element to the end of the Vektor.
      Parameters:
      index - The index we are adding to.
      missingValue - The new value we are either replacing with current or adding.
